Package: evobreed
Title: Optimal Contribution Selection for Livestock Breeding
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Austin", "Putz", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "putz.austin@gmail.com")
Author: Austin Putz [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Austin Putz <putz.austin@gmail.com>
Description: Tools for optimal contribution selection (OCS) in livestock
    breeding. Provides pedigree simulation, additive relationship matrix
    construction, and genetic algorithm-based solvers that navigate the
    Pareto frontier between genetic gain and genetic diversity (mean
    kinship). Supports both continuous contribution optimization and
    discrete mating plans with integer mating allocations and configurable
    per-sire mating limits.
